summary: I've been thinking for a while that Taylor Swift can end up as a Heroic Spirit.
body:
I’ve been thinking for a while that Taylor Swift can end up as a Heroic Spirit.

We already have a few musician type Servants (Mozart as Caster and Salieri as Avenger) and her lyrics are actually really good fight me haters.

Her Class would most likely be Caster since she isn’t known for any physical feats.

I’d give her Innocent Monster of at least B rank thanks to the bullshit media keep spouting out.

Other possible skills are in the charm type like Siren’s Song. I like Cherry/Red Lips since lipatick has become one of her trademarks alongside poetic lyricism. It would be hilarious if one of her song titles becomes a skill (say Don’t Blame Me/Getaway Car for evasion or target focus on other party member; Mine for c. star gather up; Out Of The Woods for HP recover and or NP recover).

Come to think of it, charisma or something similar would work since she has a loyal fan following. If it is charisma, it would be C or C-.

Her Noble Phantasm is a hard one to decide since it also has to be derived from a song. My top pick is between Blank Space (for obvious reasons) and Look What You Made Me Do and I Knew You Were Trouble. (We Are Never Ever Getting Back Together is too long … Sorry). Whichever it ends up being will have be a Buster type and hits a single enemy, and decreases enemy defence and attack for 3 turns,and has a chance of afflicting stun and skill seal.

I put way too much thought into this.

summary: I think I’ve posted about this 80 times but I just love it so so much. It’s been 6 months since I got this tattoo and my love...
caption:
I think I’ve posted about this 80 times but I just love it so so much. It’s been 6 months since I got this tattoo and my love for treacherous grows every time I hear it.

This song is so beautifully written and it captures the feeling of being afraid and scared but being so ready and excited to do something (which is something I really need to do more of this year!!), so perfectly.

Taylor, im so thankful to have this as a constant reminder to always do things, even if they scare me, make me anxious or I think I can’t do it.

Thankyou for writing it, I love it and you so much ❤️💛💚💙💜

@taylorswift @taylornation
